Write a C program to Traverse a Doubly Linked List (DLL) in forward direction.
Each node of the DLL contains an integer data field and two pointers:

next (points to the next node)
prev (points to the previous node)
The program should allow the user to create a DLL of n nodes, and then traverse and print the data of each node from head to tail.


Constraints:
1 ≤ n ≤ 10^5
-10^6 ≤ data ≤ 10^6

Example:
Sample Input-1:

5  
10 20 30 40 50

Sample Output-1:

10 20 30 40 50

Sample Input-2:

1  
100

Sample Output-2:

100


Explanation:
createNode(int data) creates a node with data and null pointers.
appendNode() adds a new node to the end of the DLL, updating next and prev pointers accordingly.
traverseForward() iterates from head to tail and prints each node's data.
Inputs are read at runtime, no static values.

